News International Said to Oust Sun Editor Over Phone Hacking

-- B y   A m y   T h o m s o n   a n d   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 
2011-07-22T09:40:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/news-international-said-to-oust-sun-editor-over-phone-hacking.html
News International Ltd., the
publishing arm of  News Corp. (NWSA)  embroiled in a phone-hacking
scandal, said it fired an employee in relation to his work at
the now-defunct News of the World tabloid.  The person was Matt Nixson, who was most recently features
editor at The Sun, a person familiar with the decision said,
declining to be named because the termination is part of a
police investigation into phone hacking.  News International said in a statement in fired an
unidentified employee. The Telegraph reported the identity of
the employee late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Amy Thomson in London at 
